</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Then we&#8217;re going to weave all of the conversati=
ons into a narrative that we hope can serve as the best way to get up to sp=
eed on that industry &#8212; its history, dynamics, a snapshot of the curre=
nt state, and some dreaming about what happens if things go right. </p><p s=
tyle=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0 0 20px 0;">The title Age of Miracles is a little tongue-in-cheek. I stro=
ngly believe that we can live in an Age of Miracles, but I&#8217;m also awa=
re that it&#8217;s going to take more than technological innovation to get =
there. So we explore all of the nitty-gritty, from policy to economics to c=
ulture to, of course, entrepreneurship, that&#8217;s required for a technol=
ogy to have a real positive impact on billions of lives. I hope we come out=
 the other side with a more deeply-earned optimism. </p><p style=3D"color: =
rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><=
span>For our first season, we&#8217;re starting at the foundation: </span><=
strong>energy, specifically nuclear and fusion energy. </strong></p><p styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 =
0 20px 0;">We&#8217;re unabashedly techno-optimists. More energy means more=
 growth, and growth is good. But we&#8217;re realists, too. More energy is =
great. How do we get there? </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>It&#8217;s easy to =
say, &#8220;BUILD MORE NUCLEAR.&#8221; Being pro-nuclear is an obvious posi=
tion to hold in tech at this point. But we&#8217;ve had nuclear reactors fo=
r seven decades, and its growth has stagnated in the West. Figuring out </s=
pan><em>how</em><span> to build more nuclear, how to make it cheap enough t=
hat the market demands it, is the tricky part. That&#8217;s exactly what we=
&#8217;ll cover.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">We&#8217;ll also hear from peo=
ple who are working to create energy abundance through other sources, like =
solar, wind, synthetic fuels, and even fossil fuels.&#160;</p><p style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px=
